  "context": "12 (1st official start of the academic year semester). In the exigency of service, the faculty concerned shall not avail of the equivalent release hours and carry the teaching load of the current semester as given and conformed. He/she may be compensated for the overtime services rendered as required/as necessary.\n\nSection 12 No faculty member, designated to a nonseasonal/occasional administrative work, shall be allowed to tender resignation of the designation within/during the regular duration of classes, except for medical condition and other valid reasons. His/her underload shall be treated subject to the usual accounting and auditing rules and regulations.\n\nSection 13 All non-seasonal/occasional administrative designations shall be revoked only at the beginning of the academic year.\n\nSection 14 Full-time lecturers shall be allowed to carry a maximum of thirty (30) teaching hours per week with at least three (3) or more preparations, except for the lecturers in the College of Nursing and Allied Health Sciences/ School of Midwifery, College of Maritime Education, College of Industrial Technology, College of Computing Studies, and College of Engineering. The maximum number of teaching hours shall be stretched reasonably in special case(s) when the number of units and the corresponding teaching hours could not be reduced nor split.\n\nSection 15 Part-time lecturers who wish to teach in the undergraduate program shall be allowed to carry a maximum of 15 teaching hours per week with at least 3 or more preparations.\n\nSection 16 A faculty shall be designated with a maximum of two (2) designations.\n\nSection 17 For faculty with two or more honorific designations/special positions, a three-hour deduction from the designated teaching load for every additional designation/special position shall be effected, provided that the 25% of the official time of faculty members concerned shall be credited to actual teaching load.\n\nSection 18 For faculty with 